# Non-interactive `rails credentials:edit`

When running `bin/rails credentials:edit` programmatically, override **both**
`VISUAL` and `EDITOR`. Unix convention gives `VISUAL` precedence, so setting
only `EDITOR` will fail if `VISUAL` is set to an interactive editor (e.g. vim).

```bash
VISUAL="ruby /tmp/edit_script.rb" EDITOR="ruby /tmp/edit_script.rb" \
  bin/rails credentials:edit --environment production
```
